        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "This episode is brought to you by Notion. Notion replaces the dozen tools your team is half-using. Get started at notion.com/podcast.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p07_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:f950f0601250ecdf",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 397,
        "char_start": 355,
        "episode_id": "ep-a86da8f148d3bf29",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "You resist the word 'sustainability'. Why?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p07_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:48d038c0da6395e7",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 660,
        "char_start": 417,
        "episode_id": "ep-a86da8f148d3bf29",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Because it hides the hard part. Sustainability is a systems problem \u2014 you cannot optimize one part without moving another. Fix emissions in isolation and you push the cost into water, or land, or the grid. The interactions are the whole story.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p07_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:77b8047c51ea5f8a",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 868,
        "char_start": 660,
        "episode_id": "ep-a86da8f148d3bf29",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "So it is systems thinking, first and last: manage the couplings, not the components. When we modeled a decade of interventions, the ones that failed failed because someone treated a system as a list of parts.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p07_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
